        <body>
            <div>
                <entry xml:id="Ld375c6023cf349c28e3b9dc120568670" n="12603">
                    <form>
                        <foreign xml:lang="gez">አስተሐላከሰ</foreign>
                    </form>
                    <sense xml:lang="en" source="#traces" xml:id="Tmain">
                        <cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez">
                            <quote>ʾastaḥalākasa</quote>
                        </cit>
                        <gramGrp>
                            <pos expand="verbum">v.</pos>
                        </gramGrp> meaning unknown <foreign xml:lang="gez">ወዘተርፈ፡ አስተሐላኪሶ፡ ይትበርበር፡
                            ቤቱ፡ ወይትነሣእ፡ ንዋዩ፡ ወኵሉ፡ ሕይወቱ፡ ይኩን፡ ለካልኡ፡ ዘአስተዋደዮ፡ ወረትዖ።</foreign> ‘<cit type="translation" xml:lang="fr">
                            <quote>Si quelqu’un reste..., sa maison sera pilleé, ses biens seront
                                confisqués, toute sa vie appartiendra à celui qui l’aura accusé et
                                convaincu (devant le tribunal)!</quote>
                        </cit>’ <bibl>
                            <ptr target="bm:ContiRossini1907SarsaDengel"/>
                            <citedRange unit="page"> 117 l. 34-35 (ed.)</citedRange>
                        </bibl>, <bibl>
                            <ptr target="bm:ContiRossini1907SarsaDengelV"/>
                            <citedRange unit="page"> 134 l. 6-9 (tr.)</citedRange>
                        </bibl> (<bibl>
                            <ptr target="bm:Guidi1907ReviewSarsaDengel"/>
                            <citedRange unit="page"> 225</citedRange>
                        </bibl> amends <foreign xml:lang="gez">አስተሐላኪሶ፡</foreign> to <foreign xml:lang="gez">አስተህሐንኪሶ፡</foreign> meaning “darsi per zoppo o spedato”.
                        He admits that ‘Di questa forma del verbo <foreign xml:lang="gez">ሐንከሰ፡</foreign> non conosco altro esempio (cfr. <bibl>
                            <ptr target="bm:Dillmann1907Ethiopic"/>
                            <citedRange unit="page"> 164</citedRange>
                        </bibl>) ma corrisponde bene al senso che il conteslo richiede.’ <bibl>
                            <ptr target="bm:Praetorius1910RezSarsaDengel"/>
                            <citedRange unit="page"> 621</citedRange>
                        </bibl> finds Guidi's conjecture doubtful.) </sense>
                </entry>
